article.description: Konner Frey scored 19 points and led six players in double figures as Utah Valley beat Idaho State 100-76 on Saturday night.
article.headline: Frey scores 19 points, Utah Valley beats Idaho State 100-76
article.linkText: Frey scores 19 points, Utah Valley beats Idaho State 100-76
article.story: POCATELLO, Idaho -- Konner Frey scored 19 points and led six players in double figures as Utah Valley beat Idaho State 100-76 on Saturday night. Frey also had nine rebounds for the Wolverines (4-6). Hayden Schenck added 18 points and Jaden Jackson, Ivory Young and Marcel Davis scored 14 points apiece. Dayon Goodman chipped in 11. Utah Valley trailed early in the first half but a Jackson jumper gave them the lead, 30-29, with 5:31 to go before halftime. The Wolverines finished the period on a 20-4 surge -- featuring 3-pointers by Jackson, Young and Davis -- to go up 50-33 at the break. Frey sank a pair of treys midway through the second half to help Utah Valley to a 73-52 advantage with 10:26 to play and the Wolverines cruised from there. Ali Faruq-Bey led the Bengals (3-5) with 22 points. Ben Wilson added 14 points, three assists and two rebounds.
